President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts on the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities. The appointees include Julie Ann Petty, Peter V. Berns, Jack Martin Brandt, Kenneth Capone, Micah Fialka-Feldman, Zachary W. Holler, Lisa Pugh, Michelle C. Reynolds, Deborah M. Spitalnik, Elizabeth Weintraub, and Sheryl White-Scott. These individuals have backgrounds in various fields such as advocacy, policy, research, and healthcare, and their appointments aim to serve the American people and promote inclusivity for individuals with intellectual disabilities.